text: Loreto to La Paz – 4 days, 234 miles Saturday, December 31st, 2005 In Loreto, I discovered the firehouses.
Firemen often have extra beds at their stations, and seem to be very friendly to gringos biking and talking about climate change.
Southwestern Baja is a large coastal plain, where a number of crops are grown by pumping water from deep underground.
Fields of corn grow strangely next to fields of cacti.
